cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about supervised learning and specifically focuses on the problem of learning the loss function. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of Bregman divergences, which are commonly used in optimization and information theory, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category. The paper includes experiments on image classification, indicating that cs.CV (Computer Vision) is another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the convergence of the algorithm, suggesting that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible categories.
